'''Finrún Felageómor''' was the fourth child of [[Finwë]] in the early version of the [[legendarium]].<ref name=Fin>{{SM|QA1}}, p. 213</ref> Nothing else is known about this character.

== Etymology ==
The name ''Finrún'' is in [[Old English]], since it was translated by [[Ælfwine]], but no [[Elvish]] equivalent is given.<ref name=Fin/> ''Felageómor'' is likewise an Old English name (meaning "very sorrowful").<ref name=Fin/>

In Old Norse "rún" meant "rune" or "secret";<ref>https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/r%C3%BAn#Old_Norse</ref> from this "rūn" in Old English was derived with the same meaning.<ref>"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/run#Old_English</ref>

Names ending with "rún" were more commonly associated with females (cf. "Guðrún" and "Sigrún" from the Poetic Edda).

